#3. In Turbo Stars, cats control the fighting robots they pilot.
The game's name is written in its English acronym format. It's a serious sounding name, but when pronounced out loud, the acronyms contained make the name sound more lighthearted. A connection can be seen between CATS: Crash Arena Turbo Stars and its related fighting robot game. This is because this game features robots controlled by cats with humorous expressions. Additionally, the appearance of cats and robots can be changed and new parts can be added to the feline models.

#4. Decide on your cat.
As is usual for any game, a fat cat with a sour expression greets players at the beginning of the game. It scowls as it intructs players through each step, and then demands that players reply affirmatively when asked if they are ready to fight. Creating a new cat breed is the focus of this game. However, there are a few additional tips that can help you reach the cat appearance customization screen. In truth, these aren’t many options because the game doesn’t focus on these cats. But this is enough for players to feel satisfied with their creation when they can’t even imagine anyone else creating such a unique cat.

#5. Get ready for battle by building the robot.
A robot must be added to your game with cats— the most important part. You can alter the car with a robot's customization options that include every part of the body. You can even choose each aspect of a combat-capable robot. Choosing the best possible weapon for your robot is an essential step. There are many options when it comes to firearms, but it's best to pick a weapon that fits your robot's size the best. If you select a weapon that's too large for your robot, movement will be extremely difficult. In addition to receiving loot after defeating an opponent's bot, matches also result in fighting until one side is defeated. Players earn money, items and additional cards after a victory.

#6. The duels are intense and explosive.
The battles in CATS: Crash Arena Turbo Stars are very entertaining, with intense moments that feel exciting every second. Watching an enemy lose a battle and quickly pull the parachute is something that makes players happiest. It's also very embarrassing to see a cowardly enemy parachuting away from a robot with a sad face. Warring factions vie for dominance using everything from sniping to robot turtle spinners. However, the most intriguing parts of the conflict revolve around head-banging, fist-squeezing and two robots that spin like a top. These moments are absurdly comical and help fuel one side's success. Ultimately, a victorious robot can disable their opponent's motor by spinning their own like a top. My recount of the first few frames is all I’ve shared thus far. Future scenes increase both my level of excITment and my combat prowess. I enhance both my robot and my opponent as a result. Robots possessed of immense body mass and strength blindly charge at one another. Additional firepower includes long-range projectiles, rockets and lasers.

#7. A prize awarded to the winning feline.
On top of rewards for finishing the game, you can earn small bonuses like more upgrade cards, bonus XP or robot buddies. Some premium rewards include medals, money and even extra items.

#8. Modes grant limitless competition options.
Currently, the online mode isn't completed. However, you can still play the game offline with AI, as there are several challenging levels and modes to help you progress. The Quick Fight mode as I mentioned is simply fighting, upgrading the robot then fighting again with stronger opponents. Then there's also a 2nd mode called Cats Play that offers both offline AI play and online play with friends. There are 5 leagues at higher levels of the game. These include Wood League, Iron League, Cobra League, Silver League and Gold League. The intensity of enemy aggression also changes based on which level you choose. After earning the reward, you realize how valuable it is. Imagine how your transformer would feel if he won a championship round. What does that make you feel? When a tournament's match ends, your ranking in the tournament reflects your attendance at the competition. Watching yourself climb the rankings as you defeat your rivals one by one is an exciting and gratifying experience. CATS: Crash Arena Turbo Stars is a game with attractive gameplay mechanics that encourages players to continue playing. The operation is simple and doesn't require players to hurt their brains. This is one of the reasons Google Play regularly ranks it as one of the year's top mobile games.

#9. Surpassing visuals and music defy description.
An ideal gaming position requires superior graphics with a playful, satirical, and cute nature. It should also offer 3D visual perspectives that are rich, varied and surprising.
